    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved aubergine pan to a medium heat with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced onion </strong>and <strong>half </strong>the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) and cook for 5-6 min<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>or until fragrant and beginning to soften</p><p>Once beginning to soften, add the <strong>chopped tomatoes</strong>, <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong>, <strong>bay leaf<span class=\"text-danger\">[ves]</span></strong>, <strong>half </strong>the <strong>chopped basil </strong>(save the rest for later!) and 50ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[100ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>and give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>tomato sauce</strong></p>",
