      "instruction": "<p>Slice the <strong>ciabatta<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> in half and place in the toaster for 1-2 min or until lightly toasted</p><p>Return the reserved breadcrumb pan to a high heat with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp] </span><strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>remaining chopped garlic</strong>, <strong>remaining chopped basil </strong>and <strong>toasted ciabattas </strong>cut-side down and cook for a further 1-2 min or until fragrant and charred – this is your <strong>garlic bread</strong></p>",
